<blockquote><span style="text-decoration:underline;"><strong>#4: Spike Spiegel (Cowboy Bebop)</strong></span></blockquote>
<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1796" src="https://popculturemecha.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/spike.jpg" alt="spike" width="225" height="350" />

Stop yelling at me!  Look, this is probably the only one on this list that I most likely won't ever do, so take comfort in that.  I can't get that kind of hair, suave, charisma and... yellow shirt?  He's the only guy who can pull that off, save for maybe Patrick Suaze.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<blockquote><span style="text-decoration:underline;"><strong>#3: Kyon (The Melancholy of Haruhi Suzumiya)</strong></span></blockquote>
<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1797" src="https://popculturemecha.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/kyon.jpg" alt="kyon" width="225" height="350" />

Personality-wise, Kyon is my closest match.  Down-to-earth, grounded in fact and reality, the pessimistic realist, the quick talker and slow thinker.  It'll be tough for me, but this is definitely one I want to do, at least for myself.

